      • snowflakeSort

        @Deprecated
public static <T> com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList<? extends T> snowflakeSort​(Iterable<? extends T> roots,
                                                                                     TopologicalSort.Traversable<T> traversable,
                                                                                     Comparator<T> comparator)
        Deprecated.
        This is silly. You should just use the normal sort. This is here because c/c++ link command lines are sensitive to argument order, but aren't strict about it being correct. Since they aren't strict, code has evolved to depend on the specific order that Buck has been ordering link lines, and so this preserves that legacy behavior until code that depends on it is fixed.
        This special form of topological sort returns items with each "level" sorted. The algorithm is basically this: identify all the leaves of the graph, sort them, add them to the list, remove them from the graph and proceed.
